21/05/2006
VARNA, Bulgaria -- The 13th summit of Central European heads of states, held Friday (19 May) in Varna, Bulgaria, ended with a strong show of support for continuing the EU's open-doors policy. 
Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov hosted the event, which brought together 13 regional leaders. 
In its final declaration, the summit participants called for going ahead with the EU enlargement process, starting with the accession of Bulgaria and Romania. 
The participants also discussed co-operation in energy supply security and co-ordination in the prevention and overcoming of natural disasters. 
(BNR, 24 Chasa, Hina - 20/05/06)
